body: * UIView reactive extensions for adding gesture recognizers. Thanks @akbsteam!
* Bridge missing ObjC types - fixes #481.

* Add `bidirectionalMap` to `Property` type.
* Bridge missing ObjC types - fixes #474.

* Improve type bridging in protocol proxies. Using ObjC types, like `NSString`, is no longer necessary. You can now use Swift types, like String, in method `signal(for:dispatch:)`.
* Fixed return values too.
* Improve type bridging in protocol proxies. Using ObjC types, like `NSString`, is no longer necessary. You can now use Swift types, like String, in method `signal(for:dispatch:)`.

* Update to Swift 4 syntax.

Warning: If you are still using Xcode 8, please do not update and stay on v6.3.x.

* Xcode 9 and Swift 3.2 and 4 support.

Check out this [note](https://github.com/ReactiveKit/Bond#note-xcode-9-support).
* Fix the issue with `bidirectionalMap` not working.
* Move ReactiveKit dependency to version 3.6.0.

* Fix Observable2DArray indices.
* Fix argument memory leak in protocol proxies.

* Rename `UIButton.reactive.backgroungImage` to `UIButton.reactive.backgroundImage`.
* Add `NSLayoutConstraint` to correct targets.

Thanks @dhardiman!

* Fix batch updates for NSTableView.
 
Note: This release introduces another generic argument to `DataSourceEvent<DataSource>` type -  `DataSourceEvent<DataSource, BatchKind>`. If you are using this type directly this will be a breaking change for you. You will need to update your code by replacing `DataSourceEvent<X>` with `DataSourceEvent<X, BatchKindDiff>` in your iOS (UIKit) project, or with `DataSourceEvent<X, BatchKindPatch>` in your macOS (AppKit) project.
* Fix issues with multiple observations of protocol proxy signals.
* Improve protocol proxy disposing.
* CocoaPods integration fix.
* Fix Carthage dependency.
* Fixes ReactiveKit 3.5 and Xcode 8.3 compatibility.
* Restores Swift package manager support - correctly :) Thanks @tonyarnold!
- ~~Restores Swift package manager support~~ We're looking into it, sorry!
* Add conformances to BindingExecutionContextProvider protocol.
* Adds support for bindings on non-main thread or queue.
* Fix Carthage submodules.

* Compatibility update for ReactiveKit v3.4.
* Inline binding implementation is moved to ReactiveKit as ReactiveKit is the framework that defines binding concept, while Bond is the framework that provides Cocoa binding extensions. This should not be a source breaking change, but you might need to add `import ReactiveKit` to files where inline bindings are used if you don't already have it.
* Expose `bag` property on NSObject and its subclasses. If you have a custom `let bag: DisposeBag` you can just remove it and use the provided one.
- Fix issues with automatic disposal of table and collection view bindings.

- Improve NSTableView data source event application. Thanks @tonyarnold!
- Make Diff.swift framework an explicit dependency. Might improve SourceKit stability. Thanks @tonyarnold!
- Expose `diff` operator on signals of collections.

- Fix issues where KVO observation could cause a crash.
- Make framework extensions friendly. Thanks @iandundas!
- Fix some warnings in Swift 3.1. Thanks @tonyarnold!

- API cleanup 
  - Add `ReactiveExtensions` proxy type
  - Move all extensions to the proxy
  - Refine `Deallocatable` protocol
- Enhance UITable/UICollectionView bindings
  - Allow developer to override application of array events
  - Refine the implementation
- Improve macOS bindings
